to the editor re europeans to exempt us from war court news article oct 1 the united states government 's refusal to support the international criminal court raises many questions about american foreign policy the court 's objective is to try cases of genocide gross human rights violations and crimes against humanity any person who is guilty of committing these crimes should be punished regardless of nationality with the united states leading the international campaign against terrorism it is critical that we allow our own international policies to be judged by the world community jesse raiten new york oct 1 2002

